on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com', 'nordex-online.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44684', 'http://www.nordex-online.com', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/nordex-n149-wind-turbine-web-server-sql-injection', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44684', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/nordex-n149-wind-turbine-web-server-sql-injection'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2018-25333']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2018-25332 - GitBucket 4.23.1 Unauthenticated Remote Code Execution', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 13:16:44 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-25332', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['GitBucket 4.23.1 contains an unauthenticated remote code execution vulnerability that allows attackers to execute arbitrary commands by exploiting weak secret token generation and insecure file upload functionality. Attackers can brute-force the Blowfish encryption key, upload a malicious JAR plugin via the git-lfs endpoint, and execute system commands through an exposed exploit endpoint.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2018-25332vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2018-25332weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44668', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/gitbucket-unauthenticated-remote-code-execution', 'https://github.com/gitbucket/gitbucket', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44668', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/gitbucket-unauthenticated-remote-code-execution'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2018-25332']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2018-25330 - Joomla! EkRishta 2.10 Persistent XSS and SQL Injection', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 13:16:44 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-25330', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Joomla! extension EkRishta 2.10 contains persistent cross-site scripting and SQL injection vulnerabilities that allow attackers to inject malicious code through profile fields and POST parameters. Attackers can inject script payloads in profile information fields like Address that execute when users visit the profile, or submit SQL injection payloads via the phone_no parameter to the user_setting endpoint to manipulate database queries.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2018-25330vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2018-25330weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com', 'joomlaextensions.co.in'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44660', 'http://www.joomlaextensions.co.in', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/joomla-ekrishta-persistent-xss-and-sql-injection', 'https://extensions.joomla.org/extensions/extension/living/dating-a-relationships/ek-rishta/', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44660', 'https://www.joomlaextensions.co.in/', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/joomla-ekrishta-persistent-xss-and-sql-injection'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2018-25330']}}, {'title': '日本資産総研がランサムウェア被害を公表、ファイル暗号化により情報漏えいの可能性を否定できず https://rocket-boys.co.jp/security-measures-lab/nihon-shisan-soken-ransomware-data-leak-risk/#セキュリティ対策Lab #security #DataBreach #securitynews', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 18 May 2026 01:38:17 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@securityLab_jp/116592883924491805', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['rocket-boys.co.jp'], 'email-addr': ['securityLab_jp@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': "We ended last week with an Aussie hack and now, sadly, we are starting the week with an Aussie hack.Generation Life disclosed this incident last month, though. Now, we're finally finding out who's behind it - our 'friends' at ransomware-as-a-service operation Qilin.And this is just one of FOUR hacks my colleage Daniel Croft and I are covering from over the weekend alone...#ransomware #databreach #cybersecurity https://www.cyberdaily.au/security/13608-exclusive-qilin-ransomware-group-claims-responsibility-for-generation-life-hack", 'publication_date': 'Mon, 18 May 2026 00:37:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@David_Hollingworth/116592748941836986', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cyberdaily.au'], 'email-addr': ['David_Hollingworth@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'OpenAI、TanStackへのサプライチェーン攻撃で従業員端末2台へ不正アクセス、認証 情報の一部が流出https://rocket-boys.co.jp/security-measures-lab/openai-tanstack-supply-chain-credential-leak/#セキュリティ対策Lab #security #DataBreach #securitynews', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 18 May 2026 00:37:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@securityLab_jp/116592649134198171', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['rocket-boys.co.jp'], 'email-addr': ['securityLab_jp@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Microsoft Exchange Serverのゼロデイ脆弱性 CVE-2026-42897がサイバー攻撃へ悪用https://rocket-boys.co.jp/security-measures-lab/active-exploitation-exchange-zero-day-cve-2026-42897/#セキュリティ対策Lab #security #DataBreach #securitynews', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 23:37:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@securityLab_jp/116592407663592016', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['rocket-boys.co.jp'], 'email-addr': ['securityLab_jp@mastodon.social'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-42897']}}, {'title': 'アクサ損害保険のペット保険への不正アクセス、自動車保険契約者の一部が自動登録の仕組みで6.4万件新たに判明https://rocket-boys.co.jp/security-measures-lab/axa-pet-insurance-breach-64k-auto-policyholders/#セキュリティ対策Lab #security #DataBreach #securitynews', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 23:37:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@securityLab_jp/116592368757790175', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['rocket-boys.co.jp'], 'email-addr': ['securityLab_jp@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Crime increasingly a ‘serious barrier’ to UK growth, say business leaders', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 21:59:21 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2026/may/17/crime-serious-barrier-uk-growth-business-leaders', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['The British Chambers of Commerce (BCC), which represents tens of thousands of businesses across the country, called on the government to provide “a step change in the support businesses can count on” as it said two-fifths of companies had experienced some form of crime in the past year.', 'The organisation said the government should create a cyber-attack reporting system for companies; establish regional business crime hubs that would bring together police and business crime reduction partnerships; and expand cyber and fraud resilience support for small and medium-sized businesses. It also called for more incentives for companies to invest in security.', 'Retail businesses have also complained of rising thefts. Police-recorded shoplifting rose 20% year on year to reach 516,971 offences in the year to December 2024. By March 2025, the annual total exceeded 530,000.', 'A further BCC survey carried out last autumn found that larger companies are more vulnerable to crime, increasing from 32% among microbusinesses to 58% among firms employing more than 250 people. The manufacturing sector said it was the hardest hit, with 50% of companies reporting business crime.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['booking.com.it']}}, {'title': 'Grafana Labs Refuses Extortion Demand Following GitHub Codebase BreachGrafana Labs suffered a codebase breach after an unauthorized party, claimed by the CoinbaseCartel group via a compromised GitHub token to exfiltrate internal source code and attempt extortion. The company refused the ransom demand and claims that no customer data or personal information was accessed during the incident.**** #cybersecurity #infosec #incident #databreach https://beyondmachines.net/event_details/grafana-labs-refuses-extortion-demand-following-github-codebase-breach-3-9-l-z-7/gD2P6Ple2L', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 17 May 2026 17:36:09 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@beyondmachines1/116590986396292458', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Grafana Labs suffered a codebase breach after an unauthorized party, claimed by the CoinbaseCartel group via a compromised GitHub token to exfiltrate internal source code and attempt extortion. The company refused the ransom demand and claims that no customer data or personal information was accessed during the incident.'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['beyondmachines.net']}}, {'title': 'Gîtes de France annonce à son tour avoir été visé par une cyberattaque, après les groupes Pierre et Vacances-Center Parcs et Belambra', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 18 May 2026 03:17:53 +0200', 'source': 'https://www.lemonde.fr/pixels/article/2026/05/18/gites-de-france-annonce-a-son-tour-avoir-ete-vise-par-une-cyberattaque-apres-les-groupes-pierre-et-vacances-center-parcs-et-belambra_6690376_4408996.html', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Le réseau d’hébergements Gîtes de France a confirmé, dimanche 17 mai, avoir lui aussi subi samedi un vol de données. Les informations concernant plus de 389 000 clients auraient été divulguées, selon le site de recension des fuites en ligne French Breaches, qui a révélé la cyberattaque.« Un incident de sécurité[a]entraîné un accès frauduleux à certaines données relatives aux dossiers de réservation »des clients, a annoncé Gîtes de France dans un communiqué.', 'Il s’agit du troisième acteur du tourisme en France en trois jours à communiquer sur une cyberattaque, aprèsle groupe Pierre et Vacances-Center Parcsvendredi et Belambra samedi. Le même hackeur est à l’origine des trois vols de données, a affirmé à l’Agence France-Presse le fondateur de French Breaches, qui a échangé avec lui sur une messagerie sécurisée.« Il m’a dit avoir agi pour gagner en visibilité et montrer à quel point la France est une passoire en matière de cybersécurité », a ajouté le créateur du site.', 'Le pirate a revendiqué avoir dérobé des données de réservations de Gîtes de France s’étalant sur plus de trente ans, de 1995 à 2026. Les données compromises concerneraient notamment les noms et prénoms des clients, les dates et nombre de nuitées, leurs e-mails, leurs téléphones et leurs adresses postales.« Aucune donnée bancaire n’a pu être collectée », assure Gîtes de France, qui informera lundi ses clients.', 'Le réseau a confirmé que la faille provenait de son prestataire informatique Itea, dont les logiciels sont utilisés par certaines de ses centrales de réservation départementales.« Seuls quelques départements français sont concernés », a assuré Gîtes de France. Le pirate a mentionné auprès de French Breaches la Guadeloupe, la Haute-Garonne et le Cantal.', 'Samedi, le groupe de tourisme Belambra, qui compte 44 clubs de vacances en France, avait reconnu qu’« un incident de sécurité a[vait]été identifié, ayant entraîné un accès frauduleux à une partie de nos infrastructures numériques ainsi qu’à certaines des données relatives au dossier de réservation de nos clients ».', 'Aucune donnée bancaire, aucun document d’identité ni aucun mot de passe ne sont concernés par cet incident, selon le groupe, qui ajoute avoir pris les mesures nécessaires. L’entreprise n’a pas précisé le nombre de données potentiellement exposées. Mais selon French Breaches, le hackeur revendique avoir eu accès à six mois de données : plus de 41 000 réservations détaillées, plus de 42 000 réservations clients et environ 360 000 données liées à des mineurs et enfants enregistrés dans les réservations.'], 'observables': {}}]